Package: GDSAnnotator
Type: Package
Title: Whole-genome variant annotation data manipulation using GDS files
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2025-04-27
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), gdsfmt (>= 1.32.0), SeqArray (>= 1.48.0)
Imports: methods, parallel, digest, readr, IRanges, GenomicRanges, GenomeInfoDb,
        Biostrings, S4Vectors
LinkingTo: gdsfmt
Suggests: Biobase, BiocGenerics, BiocParallel, RUnit, Rcpp, SNPRelate, crayon,
        knitr, markdown, rmarkdown, Rsamtools, VariantAnnotation
Authors@R: c(person("Xiuwen", "Zheng", role=c("aut", "cre"),
        email="xiuwen.zheng@abbvie.com", comment=c(ORCID="0000-0002-1390-0708")),
        person("Yuantao (Raven)", "Chen", role="ctb"))
Description: GDSAnnotator is designed to streamline the manipulation and integration of
        whole-genome variant annotation data using GDS files. It provides user-friendly
        functions for annotating genomic variants, supporting diverse annotation sources
        while leveraging the optimized performance of GDS-based storage. The package
        enables users to efficiently query, filter, and integrate variant annotations,
        making it a valuable resource for large-scale genomic analyses.
License: GPL-3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
ByteCompile: TRUE
LazyData: true
biocViews: Infrastructure, DataRepresentation, Sequencing, Genetics, Annotation
